805	\subsection{Cover-totality source-object identification (iter-031)}
806	
807	Step 3 (the cover-totality identification on cohomology) is more substantive than the iter-030 sketch admitted. Three obstructions surface on the iter-031 plan-agent re-probe:
808	
809	\begin{enumerate}
810	  \item \textbf{Universe mismatch}: $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$ lives in $\Type\,(u+1)$ but $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X$ lives in $\Type\,u$ — the two declarations are at different universes by design (iter-009 / iter-014). A direct $\equiv_{\Module k}$ between them does not typecheck without a universe lift.
811	  \item \textbf{Mathlib's analog is an explicit TODO}: \texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Basic.lean} (lines 31--34) lists ``if $U$ is a terminal object of $C$, define an isomorphism $(F.\mathtt{cohomologyPresheaf}\,n).\mathrm{obj}\,(\op U) \equiv_+ \mathtt{Sheaf.H}\,F\,n$'' as a TODO. We must build it ourselves.
812	  \item \textbf{The proof body is multi-step}: the natural construction goes (a) $\yoneda(\top) \cong \mathtt{const}\,\PUnit$ (terminal-collapse), (b) whisker right with $\mathtt{ModuleCat.free}\,k$ to get $\mathtt{const}\,(\mathtt{free}\,k\,\PUnit)$, (c) $(\mathtt{free}\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,\PUnit \cong \ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k$ via $\mathtt{Finsupp.LinearEquiv.finsuppUnique}$, (d) sheafify (using $\mathtt{constantSheaf}\,J\,D = \mathtt{Functor.const}\,C^{\op} \circ \mathtt{presheafToSheaf}\,J\,D$).
813	\end{enumerate}
814	
815	Iter-031 plan-agent decomposition decision: rather than tackle the full $\equiv_{\Module k}$ on cohomology (which conflates the source-iso construction, Ext-transport, and universe handling), iter-031 closes \emph{only} the source-object iso at the sheaf level. The Ext-transport step plus universe handling are deferred to iter-032+.
